55
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:49,760
The first one being that you need to frame the problem and solution in the first three screens of your app.

56
00:03:49,760 --> 00:03:56,400
The sooner the better cuz confusion honestly just kills conversions and users need to know exactly what they're getting themselves into.

57
00:03:56,400 --> 00:04:01,120
In prayer locks case, the way we do it is we welcome you and then in the second screen right there,

58
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:04,720
we tell you, hey, like, do you ever feel like your phone gets more attention than God?

59
00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:08,400
We're already framing the problem of phone addiction, social media addiction.

60
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:13,519
And then in the third screen, we give you a solution in very simple terms.

61
00:04:13,519 --> 00:04:15,280
Prayer lock helps you put God first.

62
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:21,440
So right there, we're framing the exact problem the user has, and the user knows exactly what they're going to get from the app.

63
00:04:21,440 --> 00:04:28,000
The second principle of the introduction is to give the users an aha moment in under a minute.

64
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:32,479
Hit them with a stat or realization that is very personal to them.

65
